Find out how to return to the UK from São Tomé and Príncipe
See information on how to stay safely as a visitor if you cannot return
See coronavirus travel advice for guidance on international travel
Sign up for email alerts for São Tomé and Príncipe travel advice.
There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from São Tomé and Príncipe. Charter flights and cruise ships are prohibited. See Return to the UK
For guidance on how to stay safely in São Tomé and Príncipe as a visitor if you are unable to return to the UK, see Staying during coronavirus
Entry to São Tomé and Príncipe by all foreign travellers is prohibited until at least 15 June. See Entry requirements
Consular support is limited in São Tomé and Príncipe as there is no British Embassy. The Honorary Consul/Consular Agent in São Tomé and Príncipe can offer limited consular assistance. Contact the British Embassy in Luanda, Angola who can provide consular support.
Most visits to São Tomé and Príncipe are trouble-free.
Crime rates are generally low, but armed robberies do occur. See Crime
Although there’s no recent history of terrorism in São Tomé and Príncipe, attacks can’t be ruled out. See Terrorism
You should take out comprehensive travel and medical insurance before travelling.
